mvc architecture(model view controller):-
request
controller
services
DAL
Database
Model:-Model represent the datastructure and roles
Example:-id
         name
         age
view:-view handles ui rendering
controller:-
            role of controller is to handle the request and response
            it is the brain of the application
            it is the middle layer between model and view
            call services
            sends status code and response to the client
            Example:- const,getusers=AsyncHandler(async(req,res)=>{
                const users=await User.find();
                res.status(200).json(users);
            })
Services:- What is service layer?
            ->contains business logic,validation rule,calculation and workflow
            ->it is the middle layer between controller and DAL
            ->Example:- const,getusers=AsyncHandler(async(req,res)=>{
                const users=await User.find();
                res.status(200).json(users);
            })
DAL:-Data Access Layer
            ->it handles database operations only
            ->it is the middle layer between service and database
            ->Example:- const,getusers=AsyncHandler(async(req,res)=>{
                const users=await User.find();
                res.status(200).json(users);
            })

DTO:-Data Transfer Object
            ->it is used to transfer data between layers
            ->height sensitive
            ->it is the middle layer between service and client
            ->Example:- const,getusers=AsyncHandler(async(req,res)=>{
                const users=await User.find();
                res.status(200).json(users);
            })